         <div>
            <entry xml:id="Lfc40504f75e84facb9b4da7154649ff9" n="12874">
               <form><foreign xml:lang="gez">ባረይታ</foreign></form>
               <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"><cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                     <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">bāraytā</t:quote>
                  </cit>
                  <gramGrp><pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos></gramGrp> most probably a golden
                  urinal of a high dignitary (see also the comment below) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ባረይታ፡ ፯፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="it">
                     <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">7 bāraytā</t:quote>
                  </cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Bausi1994ManoscrittiEritreaParteI"/><citedRange unit="page"> 43 VI l. 28 (ed.), 36 l. 26 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ባረይታ፡ ክልኤቱ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="it">
                     <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">due bāraytā</t:quote>
                  </cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Bausi1994ManoscrittiEritreaParteI"/><citedRange unit="page"> 44 IX l. 7–8 (ed.), 39 IX l. 10 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>
                  (‘Certamente il tigrino e amarico bārētā «urinale, vaso da notte» (<bibl><ptr target="bm:Kane1990DictAmhVol1"/><citedRange unit="page">
                     884a</citedRange></bibl> e <bibl><ptr target="bm:DaBassano1918DictTgr"/><citedRange unit="page"> 315</citedRange></bibl>). Il termine figura anche
                  nel Serʿata gebr, si veda <bibl><ptr target="bm:Kropp1988ProceedSerataGebr"/><citedRange unit="page"> 219–229 spec. 224</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="bm:Kropp1988Serata"/><citedRange unit="page"> 51–87 spec.
                        59</citedRange></bibl> «Bareta, literally a ‘urinal’ designates a vessel of
                  gold of a high dignitary», e Testo, p. 79, linea 22.’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Bausi1997ManoscrittiEritreaParteIII"/><citedRange unit="page">
                        46a–b</citedRange></bibl>) <sense n="E" xml:id="TE">Amharic <foreign xml:lang="am">ባሬታ፡</foreign>
                     <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                        <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">bāretā</t:quote>
                     </cit> ‘urinal, chamber pot for urine’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Kane1990DictAmhVol1"/><citedRange unit="page">
                           884a</citedRange></bibl>; Tigrinya <foreign xml:lang="ti">ባሬታ፡</foreign>
                     <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                        <t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">bāretā</t:quote>
                     </cit> ‘orinale, vaso da notte’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:DaBassano1918DictTgr"/><citedRange unit="page"> 315</citedRange></bibl></sense>
                  <nd/>
               </sense>
